      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARSEPT (8) looks very well placed second up from a spell. The fresh run was in much harder company at Caulfield where she was only beaten by a very progressive filly in Extragalactic. A repeat of that should win this and back to maiden grade it's no shock she's deep in the red. UPOLU (5) resumes for his second campaign. He showed ability in three runs last time in, narrowly beaten his first two outings. He's won a jumpout leading in and should be ready to go. THE BOTANY FROG (4) ran a solid race on debut at Werribee and has been given a let up since. He has upside and can improve. HARRY DE LAD (2) is off a short break in good form and can take catching with Mott aboard.",
